# Frontend Rules

## Components
- Server Components by default; Client only for events, hooks, browser APIs
- One component per file; PascalCase filename
- Accept `className` prop; use `cn()` for conditional classes
- Use CVA for variants on UI primitives

## Styling
- Tailwind CSS only — no inline styles, no CSS Modules
- Use semantic design tokens: `bg-primary`, `text-foreground`, `border-border`
- Mobile-first responsive: `grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3`

## Layout Pattern
```tsx
<Section>
  <Container>
    <SectionHeader title="..." />
    {/* content */}
  </Container>
</Section>
```

## Images
- Always use `next/image` with width, height, alt, and sizes
- Source alt text from WordPress media fields

## Don'ts
- No `<div onClick>` — use `<button>`
- No business logic in `components/ui/`
- No cross-feature imports between `components/features/` folders
